 now real code: `:build/dispatch-placement` (a construction robot
 physically places a building element) and `:handover/complete` (hand
 over the completed, inspected structure), each with its own
 double-actuation-guard boolean (`:placement-dispatched?` /
 `:handed-over?`) on the same `site` entity. The genuinely-new
 governor HARD check `permit-and-inspection-required` gates both:
 a placement requires an ISSUED BUILDING PERMIT on file, and a
 handover requires the permit AND a PASSED COMPLETION INSPECTION --
 grounded in 建築基準法 第6条（建築確認）/ 第7条（完了検査）, IBC
 §105（permit）/ §111（certificate of occupancy + final inspection）,
 and Landesbauordnung Baugenehmigung / Abnahme + EU Construction
 Products Regulation 305/2011 (cited per-jurisdiction in
 `construction.facts`, grep-verified UNIQUE fleet-wide). See
 `docs/adr/0001-architecture.md` (safety slice) and
 `docs/adr/0002-robot-dispatch-slice.md` (build slice)."}
